			"rating": 1,
			"text": {
				"text": "I had an appointment with Dr. Alpatova. The task was to replace a small filling.\n1. Non-sterile tools were used - stomatitis developed around the treated tooth within a day.\n2. A black line appeared between the tooth and the gum - the doctor suggested rinsing (which didn't help). After a week and a half, I visited another clinic where it was identified as blood trapped under the gum; an infection and minor cavity were also detected. Consequently, I had to undergo treatment again.",
				"languageCode": "en"
			},
